  ],
  "directionsTitle": "Method",
  "directionGroups": [
   {
    "title": null,
    "steps": [
     "Slice your onion into rings and fry in a little oil until translucent in a pot on the stove.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-002.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-002.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 002\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>",
     "Now fry your chicken together with the onions until browned.",
     "Add the wine, water, cloves, rosemary and thyme to the chicken. Cook the chicken until tender (about 40 minutes).<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-017.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-017.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 017\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>",
     "Take the chicken out and shred it into an ovenproof dish &#8211; don't throw away the stock you cooked the chicken in.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-031.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-031.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 031\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>",
     "Season the shredded chicken with salt and pepper.<br>",
     "Rinse the broccoli under running water.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-019.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-019.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 019\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>",
     "Now cook the broccoli until just tender in the stock you cooked the chicken in.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-029.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-029.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 029\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>",
     "Drain and place the broccoli on top of the chicken.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-046.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-046.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 046\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>",
     "In a pot on the stove, mix the milk and the mushroom soup powder and let it simmer gently for 3 minutes.",
     "Add the mayonnaise, the curry powder and the lemon juice to the mushroom soup mixture &#8211; whisk with a wire whisk so there are no lumps.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-039.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-039.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 039\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>",
     "Let it simmer for 5 minutes and pour it over the chicken and broccoli in the ovenproof dish.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-050.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-050.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 050\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>",
     "Sprinkle the cheese over.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-054.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-054.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 054\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>",
     "Bake for 40 minutes at 180 degrees Celsius.<br><a rel aria-label href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-110.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/broccoli-hoender-blog-110.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt=\"broccoli hoender blog 110\" title=\"Broccoli chicken - my kids' favourite\"></a>"
